entries.meaning: (countable) A publication, usually published daily or weekly and usually printed on cheap, low-quality paper, containing news and other articles.
(uncountable, countable) A quantity of or one of the types of paper on which newspapers are printed.

verbs.description: newspaper (third-person singular simple present newspapers, present participle newspapering, simple past and past participle newspapered)

examples: She newspapered one end of the room before painting the bookcase.

entries.meaning: (intransitive, transitive) To engage in the business of journalism
examples: His newspapered his way through the South on the sports beat, avoiding dry towns.

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete) To harass somebody through newspaper articles.
examples: He got newspapered out of public life.
